Interface Axiom.EntitySet<Y>

  • Type Parameters:
    Y - the OWL entities.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Collection<Y>, java.lang.Iterable<Y>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet<F,Y>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Classes, DataLinkSet, DataProperties, DescriptorEntitySet.EntitySetBase, DescriptorEntitySet.ExpressionEntitySetBase, DescriptorEntitySet.OWLEntitySetBase, Individuals, Literals, ObjectLinkSet, ObjectProperties, Restrictions
    Enclosing interface:
    Axiom

    public static interface Axiom.EntitySet<Y>
extends java.util.Collection<Y>
    It describe a generic set of entities managed by a specific Axiom.Descriptor. Given the descriptor's internal state (having the Axiom.EntitySet within it) and the OWL representation (i.e., queried description), it is possible to synchronise the two by using the Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent.

    • Method Detail

      • isSingleton

        boolean isSingleton()
        Describes whether this EntitySet contains a single element. If yes, the synchronisation procedure will replace always such an element.
        Returns:
        (true) if this is a singleton set, (false) otherwise.

      • setSingleton

        void setSingleton(boolean singleton)
        Set this EntitySet to contain a single element. If yes, the synchronisation procedure will replace always such an element.
        Parameters:
        singleton - (true) if this is a singleton set, (false) otherwise.

      • synchroniseTo

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<Y> synchroniseTo(Axiom.EntitySet<Y> queried)
        This method is used during Axiom.Descriptor.writeAxioms() and finds the differences between the actual state of EntitySet and the one queried to the OWL representation. Such changes represent the intent to delete and add axioms to the OWL structure, to make it equal to this EntitySet.
        Parameters:
        queried - the set to check for writing differences from OWL to this EntitySet.
        Returns:
        the changes to be applied in the ontology to make this EntitySet equal to the one queried to the OWL representation.

      • synchroniseFrom

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<Y> synchroniseFrom(Axiom.EntitySet<Y> queried)
        This method is used during Axiom.Descriptor.readAxioms() and finds the differences between the actual state of EntitySet and the one queried to the OWL representation. Such changes represents the intent to delete and add elements to this EntitySet, to make it equal to the OWL representation.
        Parameters:
        queried - the set to check for reading differences from OWL to this EntitySet.
        Returns:
        the changes to be applied in this EntitySet to make it equal to the one queried to the OWL representation.
